                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/6286: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Diplomatic Agent and Consul General at Tangier</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">White</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-29T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 29, 1940—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>64. Your 39, October 28, 7 p.m. Consul at Dakar reported October 27 that General
                    Weygand had arrived there October 26. Accordingly, there would appear to be no
                    further question of your acting as intermediary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
